This is a port of classic +acts_as_list+ to Mongo Mapper.

It has (almost) the same functionality and passes the original test-suite. 
Scope needs to be defined as symbol or array of symbols.


ActsAsList
==========

This acts_as extension provides the capabilities for sorting and reordering a number of objects in a list. If you do not specify custom position +column+ in the options, a key named +position+ will be used automatically.


Example
=======

  class TodoList
    has_many :todo_items, :order => "position"
  end

  class TodoItem
    
    include MongoMapper::Document
    
    plugin MongoMapper::Plugins::ActsAsList
    
    key :todo_list_id, ObjectId
    belongs_to :todo_list

    acts_as_list :scope => :todo_list_id

  end

  todo_list.first.move_to_bottom
  todo_list.last.move_higher


